item.media:title: Adorable dogs Mt. Fuji Shiro-nii-san and Kuroo-san having fun in bubble bath
item.media:description:
Bath time is a special bonding moment for dogs, and it's always a joy to watch them have fun in the bubbles. In a recent video shared by @buchrubuchru, we see two adorable pups, Mt. Fuji Shiro-nii-san and Kuroo-san, enjoying their bath time in Tokyo, Japan.
The video starts with Mt. Fuji Shiro-nii-san, the older of the two dogs, leisurely relaxing in the tub while the bubbles gently surround him. It's clear that he truly enjoys his bath time, as he closes his eyes and lets out a contented sigh.
But the younger pup, Kuroo-san, can't help but be envious of his older brother's bubble bath. He desperately wants to join in on the fun and can be seen trying to climb into the tub to join his brother.
item.media:keywords: dog, animals, pet, bubble, bath, Mt. Fuji, relax, brother, Japan

item.media:title: Incredible shot of lightning captured in Cleveland.
item.media:description:
Nature never fails to amaze us with its powerful and awe-inspiring displays. A recent video captured by @MikeACollier in Cleveland, Ohio, is a perfect example of this. The footage shows an incredible shot of lightning illuminating the dark sky, illuminating the land below in a brilliant burst of light.
The lightning strike is truly spectacular, as it lights up the sky in a beautiful and mesmerizing display. The bright bolts of lightning are clearly visible against the dark clouds, and the way they dance across the sky is truly mesmerizing.
According to @MikeACollier, the lightning was spectacular across the land and he was able to catch this breathtaking video in Cleveland, Ohio. He captured the moment with expertise and skill, capturing the full splendor of the natural phenomenon.
This video is a reminder of the raw power and beauty of nature, and it's a true testament to the skill of @MikeACollier as a videographer.
item.media:keywords: incredible, lightning, shot, fascinating, land, Cleveland, USA

item.media:title: The drunk man took revenge on the barrier gate after it hit him!
item.media:description:
The incident took place in the village of Borovlyany near Minsk. The police received information that an unknown person damaged the barrier in the courtyard of the house. Thanks to CCTV cameras, the culprit was found.
It turned out that a drunken 53-year-old man was returning from a friend's house that evening. And when he passed next to the barrier, the device touched him when closing. The man decided to take revenge on the "offender".
First, the man hit the barrier several times and left. But after a while he returned and continued to "beat" the mechanism. In total, more than 20 strikes were made on the device. The damage amounted to about 1000 Belarusian rubles.
item.media:keywords: drunk, man, barrier, gate, revenge, hit, village, Police, offender, beat, rubles

The store employee reported the incident to the director, who filed a complaint of robbery on January 7th with the Police Department. On January 13, the suspect was arrested. It turned out to be a 19-year-old resident of the Zaeltsovsky district. The guy has already been prosecuted before.

item.media:title: The car was driving along the street without a driver!
item.media:description:
People in Baranovichi saw a moving car that didn't have a driver, and they pushed it down the street. It was found out that the car's owner had left it near the store without lifting the handbrake and then gone shopping. Regional traffic police say that he had a remote control in his pocket that he accidentally pressed, which made the car move.
Thankfully, the situation was defused when concerned passersby pulled over the car. No one was hurt, and the cars weren't damaged. The negligent driver has been held accountable by the proper authorities.
item.media:keywords: car, driver, street, shop, police, control, damage, authorities

item.media:description: The Author said: "Our cat actually has a special story. She is a rescue kitten that was brutally attacked as a baby and spent the first part of her life undergoing surgeries to repair her backside. Once we adopted her, she ended up with another serious lung infection that put her in the ICU for a week. Then she got another serious bone infection, and the vet had to remove part of her jaw. She is a true miracle cat. Her name is Black Frances. She is 11 months old and full of attitude. And we call her "one in a million" because her video has gotten more than a million views. She loves playing with our piano and enjoys the sound that she produces". Credit to: @joshuathepost
